    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener><dateline><date when="1921-05-18">May 18, 1921</date></dateline>
                    <salute>My dear <persName key="richard_aldington">Richard</persName>:</salute></opener>
                    <p><persName key="amy_lowell">Amy</persName> received your letter just before she had to undergo her fourth <rs key="medical" type="theme">operation</rs>.
                    You will be delighted to know that it is over and that she is recovering. The
                    doctors say that this time they feel it surely will be successful which we all
                    pray.</p>
                    <p>She was awfully rushed just before she had to go to bed as <persName key="florence_ayscough">Mrs. Ayscough</persName> was
                    here from <placeName key="china">China</placeName>, and they worked against time at the Chinese translations.
                    We hope to come to <placeName key="england">England</placeName> <date when="1922">next Spring</date>. It will be very pleasant to see you
                    again. As soon as Amy is well enough, she will write to you herself.</p>
                    <closer>Sincerely yours,</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
